Defendant Jacob Matthew Schneider in court with attorney Daniel Gordon Mitchell.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve 3 MONTHS in the House of Correction;sentence stayed commence on June 3, 2016 by 5:00 pm .

Court sentenced defendant to pay a FINE of $350.00  PLUS all costs, penalties and surcharges by 11-30-2016  or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Court ordered the defendant to pay restitution to the City of West Allis in the amount of $17.50 by 11-30-2016.

Court ordered Intoxicated Driver Assessment; form filed; copy to defendant.
Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for 18 months.
Court ordered any vehicle owned/operated by the defendant to be equipped with the Ignition Interlock Device for 18 months.

AS TO COUNT 3:  Defendant sentenced to serve 8 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 24 MONTHS.
Conditions:
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  Successfully complete a course in anger management;
*  No contact with Lois P. or Taresar C.;
*  Obtain a mental health evaluation/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Obtain/maintain full time employment/school;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges by 11-30-2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

AS TO COUNT 4:  Court ordered defendant to pay a FINE of $100.00 INCLUDING ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by 11-30-2016 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
